</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulanaesoulsease.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulanae Soulsease</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 539<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/01 8:18:38 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.wwa.com/~danas/Kulanae5.gif height=158 width=119></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Everquest 2 slated for future?</span><hr size=1> The only way this will work is a forced character transfer to the new EQ2 servers.  If not they will experience the same issues that killed the UO2 project:<br>
<br>
1) You have an established customer base playing EQ1.<br>
<br>
2) You have immense sunk costs in servers and bandwidth for EQ1.<br>
<br>
3) You will have additional sunk costs for servers and bandwidth for EQ2.<br>
<br>
4) If your customer base doesn't double and you continue to maintain both EQ1 and EQ2 concurrently you have doubled your expenses and are now losing money in relation to maintaining only EQ1.<br>
<br>
No way I'm going to start all over on EQ2 just to play the same content on EQ1 with better graphics.  Now if Verant wants to move me with all my equipment and such to the EQ2 servers I'd love to see a revamped Everquest. But if I am going to start from scratch it will be on a different game. <p><font size=2 face="Tempus Sans ITC, Verdana, Helvetica">
Kulanae Soulsease</font><br>
