You know, there's no guarantee that EQ2 is going to be a PC game.<br>
<br>
I had a phone interview with Verant about a year ago and the job would have been working on a PS2 version of EQ designed to be played by a more casual player with faster advancement, different combat, etc.  It didn't really seem like a game to replace EQ, but a different game leveraging the EQ name.<br>
<br>
I'm kinda happy that interview didn't go anywhere.  My game will be on the store shelves before Thanksgiving and they haven't even announced that one yet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Bahd - Level 57 monk<BR>
